      "width": 5880
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-2-3- When fluid free of air comes out, close the bleeding screw 3 of the Boost Piston",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(64,0,64)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 600,
      "top": 2640,
      "height": 240,
      "width": 6600
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-4-1- Maintain the device providing 2bar of pressure in the reservoir With No Brake Pedal Pressed",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(64,0,64)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 600,
      "top": 5280,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 8280
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-4-2- Open the bleeder screw 3 of the Boost Piston",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(64,0,64)",
